dataset.description: Bills of lading header information for incoming shipments regulated by U.S. Customs and Border Protection's Automated Manifest System (AMS) for 2018.

fields.description: Unique shipment identifier. Can be used as the key to link to more detailed Bill of Lading, Cargo Description, & Hazardous Materials tables.
fields.name: identifier

fields.description: Date that the trade added, updated or deleted the record.
fields.name: trade_update_date

fields.description: Date that the data extract is produced.
fields.name: run_date

fields.description: A valid conveyance name entered using no slashes.
fields.name: vessel_name

fields.description: A code representing the US. Customs district/port.
fields.name: port_of_unlading

fields.description: A date representing the original scheduled date of arrival (for imports) or departure (for exports) at this port.
fields.name: estimated_arrival_date

fields.description: A code representing the foreign port in which cargo was laden on board with the conveyance destined to the U.S.
fields.name: foreign_port_of_lading

fields.description: Whether the record is New, Updated, or has been Deleted. Any records marked deleted should not be counted in any summations or rankings.
fields.name: record_status_indicator

fields.description: Location where the shippers first took possession of the cargo.
fields.name: place_of_receipt

fields.description: Final port of destination if the cargo travels by ship beyond its initial port of unlading in the United States.
fields.name: port_of_destination

fields.description: Foreign port of destination for goods passing through the United States while in transit to their final international port.
fields.name: foreign_port_of_destination

fields.description: The Standard Carrier Alpha Code (SCAC) or automated FIRMS of the secondary notify party authorized to receive a copy of the bill of lading notification.
fields.name: secondary_notify_party_1

fields.description: The date on which the conveyance was actually arrived at the first U.S. port.
fields.name: actual_arrival_date

fields.description: The company or person receiving the items.
fields.name: consignee_name

fields.description: Consignee's address, if available.
fields.name: consignee_address

fields.description: Consignee Contact Name
fields.name: consignee_contact_name

fields.description: Consignee communication type. One of the following codes identifying the types of communications number provided where EM = e-mail address, FX = Facsimile Number, TE = Telephone Number
fields.name: consignee_comm_number_qualifier

fields.description: e-mail, facsimile or telephone number for the contact name provided.
fields.name: consignee_comm_number

fields.description: The company or person shipping the items.
fields.name: shipper_party_name

fields.description: Shipper Address, if available.
fields.name: shipper_address

fields.description: Shipper Contact Name
fields.name: shipper_contact_name

fields.description: Shipper communication type. One of the following codes identifying the types of communications number provided where EM = e-mail address, FX = Facsimile Number, TE = Telephone Number
fields.name: shipper_comm_number_qualifier

fields.description: e-mail, facsimile or telephone number for the contact name provided.
fields.name: shipper_comm_number

fields.description:
A container/equipment number associated with the bill of lading. This container/equipment number must reflect the number exactly as
it physically appears on the container. Indicate NC for
noncontainerized freight. Neither an identical container/equipment
number nor the designation NC should be repeated within the same bill.
fields.name: container_number

fields.description: Description Sequence Number where numbers range from 001­ - 999.
fields.name: description_sequence_number

fields.description: The total number of pieces in the container being described. If count is less than 10 digits, right justify with leading zeroes.
fields.name: piece_count

fields.description: A description of the cargo.
fields.name: description_text

fields.description: The code located in the Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States Annotated that represents the tariff number or Harmonized Tariff Schedule B that represents the commodity export. On import manifests, the Harmonized Code is mandatory for paperless entry types (62 (T/E) and 63 (IE) for waterborne export shipments.
fields.name: harmonized_number

fields.description: A value greater than zero, in whole dollars, of the commodity. Twenty dollars per kilo may be used if the value is unknown. If value is less than 8 digits, right justify with leading zeros.
fields.name: harmonized_value

fields.description: A value greater than zero representing the net weight in pounds or kilos of the commodity. If weight is less than 10 digits, right justify with leading zeros.
fields.name: harmonized_weight

fields.description: A code representing the unit of measure. Valid codes are: LB or L = pounds, KG or K = Kilograms, LT or T = Long Ton, ST or S = Short Ton, ET or E = Metric Ton, MT or M = Measurement Ton, GM or G = Grams, OZ or O = Ounces. If measurement unit is less than 3 characters, left justify.
fields.name: harmonized_weight_unit

fields.description: An Enigma assigned serial id.
fields.name: serial_28ad5b7c_f553_470f_a0bd_36fca57a6021
